## Key Learnings
- prompts must be tested multiple times to evaluate reliability
- output constraints are critical for consistency
- few-shot examples strongly improve classification tasks
- structured formats are essential for data extraction
- over-constraining prompts can lead to incorrect outputs
- different task types require different prompt strategies

